22}}\n* {{Allmusic|id=4765}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0005153}}\n* {{Rockhall}}\n* {{Pop Chronicles|6}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130513034924/http://www.wmeentertainment.com/little_richard/summary/ Little Richard Booking Agency]\n\n<!--Although \"Little Richard\" is a stage name, it is a name nonetheless, which means that the correct sort key is \"Little Richard\". See [[Poly Styrene]] and [[Black Randy]] for other examples. -->\n{{Portal bar|Biography|United States|Rock music}}\n{{Little Richard}}\n{{Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award}}\n{{1986 Rock and Roll Hall of Fame}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Little Richard}}\n[[Category:1932 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American pianists]]\n[[Category:African-American Christians]]\n[[Category:African-American male singers]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:African-American pianists]]\n[[Category:African-American rock musicians]]\n[[Category:African-American rock singers]]\n[[Category:African-American songwriters]]\n[[Category:American rhythm and blues singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American rock pianists]]\n[[Category:American male pianists]]\n[[Category:American rock singers]]\n[[Category:American rock songwriters]]\n[[Category:American male songwriters]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American soul singers]]\n[[Category:American Seventh-day Adventists]]\n[[Category:Converts to Adventism]]\n[[Category:Bisexual men]]\n[[Category:Bisexual musicians]]\n[[Category:Brunswick Records artists]]\n[[Category:Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award winners]]\n[[Category:LGBT African Americans]]\n[[Category:LGBT musicians from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:LGBT Protestants]]\n[[Category:LGBT singers]]\n[[Category:LGBT songwriters]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mercury Records artists]]\n[[Category:Okeh Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Macon, Georgia]]\n[[Category:RCA Records artists]]\n[[Category:Ro